body:
verilator version: 4.214
steps of reproduction:
```
// file: x.sv
module x();
	byte b[$] = {1, 2, 3};
	byte v;
    initial begin
    	v = b.and();
        $display("%d", v);
        $finish;
    end
endmodule
```
which gives following error:
```
%Error: x.sv:5:17: syntax error, unexpected ';', expecting with-then-(
    5 |      v = b.and();
      |                 ^
%Error: Exiting due to 1 error(s)
```
I changed verilog.y:4120 from
```
array_methodWith<nodep>:
		array_methodNoRoot			{ $$ = $1; }
```
to
```
array_methodWith<nodep>:
		array_methodNoRoot parenE		{ $$ = $1; }
```
and the problem seems to be fixed, not sure if it is the right way though.
